	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: anybody put a fat ds's backlit screen in gba original?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I believe what he meant is that the original DS LCD has been transplanted into a DS Lite. Why in the world you'd do that is beyond me.<br /><br />If he means the DS Lite LCD has been used in a GBA, the main problem is the physical dimension differences. If you feed it a signal as-is, I can almost promise you that it'll just be a 240x160 box in the top-left of the LCD, with the border on the right and bottom being garbled repeated lines from another frame or some other don't-care-condition anomaly.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


